description.narrative: In view of the multiple risks facing Uganda, including those related to population movements, disease outbreaks and climate hazards, UNICEF prioritization of emergency preparedness at national and sub-national levels proved crucial in 2019. The Emergency Preparedness Platform and Child Centred Risk Analysis allowed UNICEF to plan its activities with analysis of, and preparedness for, localized risks at the forefront of its programming and system strengthening approach. UNICEF actively engaged in policy discourse on the inclusion of refugees in national systems including through the development of costed, integrated sector response plans. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:30/12/2019
